{#- Site footer — LOCKED grammar §2 row 10 (design lock 2026-07-07), C's dark
    editorial footer: brandrow + nav, the bound §4a colophon line, then the
    compliance grammar with its RESERVED slots (round-2 grade finding 6, now
    part of the locked grammar): DMCA link (in nav), Equal Housing mark, MLS
    attribution slot, Fair Housing statement slot (Plan §2 row 11).
    Studio NAME stays a placeholder pending the operator's naming reconcile
    (plan §11.5). Headings-free by design (nav landmarks carry structure). -#}
<footer class="site-footer">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="footer-brandrow">
      <span class="b">Everlane Realty</span>
      <nav class="footer-nav" aria-label="Footer">
        {%- for item in nav.footerExplore %}
        <a href="{{ item.url }}">{{ item.title }}</a>
        {%- endfor %}
        {%- for item in nav.footerFinePrint %}
        <a href="{{ item.url }}">{{ item.title }}</a>
        {%- endfor %}
      </nav>
    </div>
    {#- The §4a bound colophon line — exact copy, do not paraphrase. Studio name
        RULED "Selenko" by the operator 2026-07-08 (his brand/company for the studio
        behind the automation; closes the plan §11.5 naming reconcile). -#}
    <p class="footer__studio">Run by Selenko, Everlane&rsquo;s own studio automation &mdash; every client-facing decision is the broker&rsquo;s. <a href="/ai/">See how this site runs &rarr;</a></p>
    <p class="footer__nap">
      Everlane Realty &middot; {{ site.broker.street }}, {{ site.broker.city }}, {{ site.broker.state }} {{ site.broker.zip }} &middot;
      <a href="tel:{{ site.broker.phoneHref }}">{{ site.broker.phone }}</a> &middot;
      <a href="mailto:{{ site.broker.email }}">{{ site.broker.email }}</a> &middot;
      {{ site.broker.name }}, {{ site.broker.title }} &middot; License #{{ site.broker.license }}
    </p>
    {% include "components/footer-legal.njk" %}
  </div>
</footer>
